xt-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">I know the Yorkshire Dales in by gone times as a boy I walked and cycled the Green Lanes and my memories of those years are much treasured.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">I am greatly concerned for our environmental heritage and have supported the work of the John Muir Trust, Scottish Natural Heritage, the National Trust for Scotland and Historic Scotland, the Field Studies Council and the National Parks of England, Wales and Scotland. I am now 80 and not so physically active as of yore. This letter is an appeal to the Government to protect our precious environment. I apologise for straining your eyesight.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">9 September 13</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>